57 void CreateMapForType(Isolate* isolate, const WasmModule* module,
58  ModuleTypeIndex type_index,
59  DirectHandle<FixedArray> maybe_shared_maps) {
60  // Recursive calls for supertypes may already have created this map.
61  if (IsMap(maybe_shared_maps->get(type_index.index))) return;
62 
63  CanonicalTypeIndex canonical_type_index =
64  module->canonical_type_id(type_index);
65 
66  // Try to find the canonical map for this type in the isolate store.
67  DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> canonical_rtts =
68  direct_handle(isolate->heap()->wasm_canonical_rtts(), isolate);
69  DCHECK_GT(static_cast<uint32_t>(canonical_rtts->length()),
70  canonical_type_index.index);
71  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_canonical_map =
72  canonical_rtts->get(canonical_type_index.index);
73  if (!maybe_canonical_map.IsCleared()) {
74  maybe_shared_maps->set(type_index.index,
75  maybe_canonical_map.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
76  return;
77  }
78 
79  DirectHandle<Map> rtt_parent;
80  // If the type with {type_index} has an explicit supertype, make sure the
81  // map for that supertype is created first, so that the supertypes list
82  // that's cached on every RTT can be set up correctly.
83  ModuleTypeIndex supertype = module->supertype(type_index);
84  if (supertype.valid()) {
85  // This recursion is safe, because kV8MaxRttSubtypingDepth limits the
86  // number of recursive steps, so we won't overflow the stack.
87  CreateMapForType(isolate, module, supertype, maybe_shared_maps);
88  // We look up the supertype in {maybe_shared_maps} as a shared type can only
89  // inherit from a shared type and vice verca.
90  rtt_parent = direct_handle(
91  Cast<Map>(maybe_shared_maps->get(supertype.index)), isolate);
92  }
93  DirectHandle<Map> map;
94  switch (module->type(type_index).kind) {
95  case TypeDefinition::kStruct: {
96  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context_independent;
97  map = CreateStructMap(isolate, canonical_type_index, rtt_parent,
98  context_independent);
99  break;
100  }
101  case TypeDefinition::kArray:
102  map = CreateArrayMap(isolate, canonical_type_index, rtt_parent);
103  break;
104  case TypeDefinition::kFunction:
105  map = CreateFuncRefMap(isolate, canonical_type_index, rtt_parent,
106  module->type(type_index).is_shared);
107  break;
108  case TypeDefinition::kCont:
109  UNIMPLEMENTED();
110  }
111  canonical_rtts->set(canonical_type_index.index, MakeWeak(*map));
112  maybe_shared_maps->set(type_index.index, *map);
113 }

117 bool CompareWithNormalizedCType(const CTypeInfo& info,
118  CanonicalValueType expected,
119  CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation int64_rep) {
120  MachineType t = MachineType::TypeForCType(info);
121  // Wasm representation of bool is i32 instead of i1.
122  if (t.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kBool) {
123  return expected == kWasmI32;
124  }
125  if (info.GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString) {
126  // WebAssembly does not support one byte strings in fast API calls as
127  // runtime type checks are not supported so far.
128  return false;
129  }
130 
131  if (t.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
132  if (int64_rep == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt) {
133  return expected == kWasmI64;
134  }
135  DCHECK_EQ(int64_rep, CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kNumber);
136  return expected == kWasmI32 || expected == kWasmF32 || expected == kWasmF64;
137  }
138  return t.representation() == expected.machine_representation();
139 }

141 enum class ReceiverKind { kFirstParamIsReceiver, kAnyReceiver };
142 
143 bool IsSupportedWasmFastApiFunction(Isolate* isolate,
144  const wasm::CanonicalSig* expected_sig,
145  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
146  ReceiverKind receiver_kind,
147  int* out_index) {
148  if (!shared->IsApiFunction()) {
149  return false;
150  }
151  if (shared->api_func_data()->GetCFunctionsCount() == 0) {
152  return false;
153  }
154  if (receiver_kind == ReceiverKind::kAnyReceiver &&
155  !shared->api_func_data()->accept_any_receiver()) {
156  return false;
157  }
158  if (receiver_kind == ReceiverKind::kAnyReceiver &&
159  !IsUndefined(shared->api_func_data()->signature())) {
160  // TODO(wasm): CFunctionInfo* signature check.
161  return false;
162  }
163 
164  const auto log_imported_function_mismatch = [&shared, isolate](
165  int func_index,
166  const char* reason) {
167  if (v8_flags.trace_opt) {
168  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
169  PrintF(scope.file(), "[disabled optimization for ");
170  ShortPrint(*shared, scope.file());
171  PrintF(scope.file(),
172  " for C function %d, reason: the signature of the imported "
173  "function in the Wasm module doesn't match that of the Fast API "
174  "function (%s)]\n",
175  func_index, reason);
176  }
177  };
178 
179  // C functions only have one return value.
180  if (expected_sig->return_count() > 1) {
181  // Here and below, we log when the function we call is declared as an Api
182  // function but we cannot optimize the call, which might be unexpected. In
183  // that case we use the "slow" path making a normal Wasm->JS call and
184  // calling the "slow" callback specified in FunctionTemplate::New().
185  log_imported_function_mismatch(0, "too many return values");
186  return false;
187  }
188 
189  for (int c_func_id = 0, end = shared->api_func_data()->GetCFunctionsCount();
190  c_func_id < end; ++c_func_id) {
191  const CFunctionInfo* info =
192  shared->api_func_data()->GetCSignature(isolate, c_func_id);
193  if (!compiler::IsFastCallSupportedSignature(info)) {
194  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id,
195  "signature not supported by the fast API");
196  continue;
197  }
198 
199  CTypeInfo return_info = info->ReturnInfo();
200  // Unsupported if return type doesn't match.
201  if (expected_sig->return_count() == 0 &&
202  return_info.GetType() != CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid) {
203  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id, "too few return values");
204  continue;
205  }
206  // Unsupported if return type doesn't match.
207  if (expected_sig->return_count() == 1) {
208  if (return_info.GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid) {
209  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id, "too many return values");
210  continue;
211  }
212  if (!CompareWithNormalizedCType(return_info, expected_sig->GetReturn(0),
213  info->GetInt64Representation())) {
214  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id, "mismatching return value");
215  continue;
216  }
217  }
218 
219  if (receiver_kind == ReceiverKind::kFirstParamIsReceiver) {
220  if (expected_sig->parameter_count() < 1) {
221  log_imported_function_mismatch(
222  c_func_id, "at least one parameter is needed as the receiver");
223  continue;
224  }
225  if (!expected_sig->GetParam(0).is_reference()) {
226  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id,
227  "the receiver has to be a reference");
228  continue;
229  }
230  }
231 
232  int param_offset =
233  receiver_kind == ReceiverKind::kFirstParamIsReceiver ? 1 : 0;
234  // Unsupported if arity doesn't match.
235  if (expected_sig->parameter_count() - param_offset !=
236  info->ArgumentCount() - 1) {
237  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id, "mismatched arity");
238  continue;
239  }
240  // Unsupported if any argument types don't match.
241  bool param_mismatch = false;
242  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < expected_sig->parameter_count() - param_offset;
243  ++i) {
244  int sig_index = i + param_offset;
245  // Arg 0 is the receiver, skip over it since either the receiver does not
246  // matter, or we already checked it above.
247  CTypeInfo arg = info->ArgumentInfo(i + 1);
248  if (!CompareWithNormalizedCType(arg, expected_sig->GetParam(sig_index),
249  info->GetInt64Representation())) {
250  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id, "parameter type mismatch");
251  param_mismatch = true;
252  break;
253  }
254  START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
255  if (arg.GetSequenceType() == CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence) {
256  log_imported_function_mismatch(c_func_id,
257  "sequence types are not allowed");
258  param_mismatch = true;
259  break;
260  }
261  END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
262  }
263  if (param_mismatch) {
264  continue;
265  }
266  *out_index = c_func_id;
267  return true;
268  }
269  return false;
270 }

272 bool ResolveBoundJSFastApiFunction(const wasm::CanonicalSig* expected_sig,
273  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable) {
274  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
275 
276  DirectHandle<JSFunction> target;
277  if (IsJSBoundFunction(*callable)) {
278  auto bound_target = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(callable);
279  // Nested bound functions and arguments not supported yet.
280  if (bound_target->bound_arguments()->length() > 0) {
281  return false;
282  }
283  if (IsJSBoundFunction(bound_target->bound_target_function())) {
284  return false;
285  }
286  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> bound_target_function(
287  bound_target->bound_target_function(), isolate);
288  if (!IsJSFunction(*bound_target_function)) {
289  return false;
290  }
291  target = Cast<JSFunction>(bound_target_function);
292  } else if (IsJSFunction(*callable)) {
293  target = Cast<JSFunction>(callable);
294  } else {
295  return false;
296  }
297 
298  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(target->shared(), isolate);
299  int api_function_index = -1;
300  // The fast API call wrapper currently does not support function overloading.
301  // Therefore, if the matching function is not function 0, the fast API cannot
302  // be used.
303  return IsSupportedWasmFastApiFunction(isolate, expected_sig, *shared,
304  ReceiverKind::kAnyReceiver,
305  &api_function_index) &&
306  api_function_index == 0;
307 }

314  return type.is_abstract_ref() && type.generic_kind() == GenericKind::kExtern;

317 bool IsStringOrExternRef(wasm::CanonicalValueType type) {

321 bool IsDataViewGetterSig(const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig,
322  wasm::CanonicalValueType return_type) {
323  return sig->parameter_count() == 3 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
324  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
325  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
326  sig->GetParam(2) == wasm::kWasmI32 && sig->GetReturn(0) == return_type;
327 }
328 
329 bool IsDataViewSetterSig(const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig,
330  wasm::CanonicalValueType value_type) {
331  return sig->parameter_count() == 4 && sig->return_count() == 0 &&
332  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
333  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmI32 && sig->GetParam(2) == value_type &&
334  sig->GetParam(3) == wasm::kWasmI32;
335 }

337 const MachineSignature* GetFunctionSigForFastApiImport(
338  Zone* zone, const CFunctionInfo* info) {
339  uint32_t arg_count = info->ArgumentCount();
340  uint32_t ret_count =
341  info->ReturnInfo().GetType() == CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid ? 0 : 1;
342  constexpr uint32_t param_offset = 1;
343 
344  MachineSignature::Builder sig_builder(zone, ret_count,
345  arg_count - param_offset);
346  if (ret_count) {
347  sig_builder.AddReturn(MachineType::TypeForCType(info->ReturnInfo()));
348  }
349 
350  for (uint32_t i = param_offset; i < arg_count; ++i) {
351  sig_builder.AddParam(MachineType::TypeForCType(info->ArgumentInfo(i)));
352  }
353  return sig_builder.Get();
354 }

356 // This detects imports of the forms:
357 // - `Function.prototype.call.bind(foo)`, where `foo` is something that has a
358 // Builtin id.
359 // - JSFunction with Builtin id (e.g. `parseFloat`, `Math.sin`).
360 WellKnownImport CheckForWellKnownImport(
361  DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data, int func_index,
362  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable, const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig) {
363  WellKnownImport kGeneric = WellKnownImport::kGeneric; // "using" is C++20.
364  if (trusted_instance_data.is_null()) return kGeneric;
365  // Check for plain JS functions.
366  if (IsJSFunction(*callable)) {
367  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = Cast<JSFunction>(*callable)->shared();
368  if (!sfi->HasBuiltinId()) return kGeneric;
369  // This needs to be a separate switch because it allows other cases than
370  // the one below. Merging them would be invalid, because we would then
371  // recognize receiver-requiring methods even when they're (erroneously)
372  // being imported such that they don't get a receiver.
373  switch (sfi->builtin_id()) {
374  // =================================================================
375  // String-related imports that aren't part of the JS String Builtins
376  // proposal.
377  case Builtin::kNumberParseFloat:
378  if (sig->parameter_count() == 1 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
379  IsStringRef(sig->GetParam(0)) &&
380  sig->GetReturn(0) == wasm::kWasmF64) {
381  return WellKnownImport::kParseFloat;
382  }
383  break;
384 
385  // =================================================================
386  // Math functions.
387 #define COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(name) \
388  case Builtin::kMath##name: { \
389  if (!v8_flags.wasm_math_intrinsics) return kGeneric; \
390  const FunctionSig* builtin_sig = WasmOpcodes::Signature(kExprF64##name); \
391  if (!builtin_sig) { \
392  builtin_sig = WasmOpcodes::AsmjsSignature(kExprF64##name); \
393  } \
394  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(builtin_sig); \
395  if (EquivalentNumericSig(sig, builtin_sig)) { \
396  return WellKnownImport::kMathF64##name; \
397  } \
398  break; \
399  }
400 
401  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Acos)
402  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Asin)
403  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Atan)
404  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Atan2)
405  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Cos)
406  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Sin)
407  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Tan)
408  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Exp)
409  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Log)
410  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Pow)
411  COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64(Sqrt)
412 
413 #undef COMPARE_MATH_BUILTIN_F64
414 
415  default:
416  break;
417  }
418  return kGeneric;
419  }
420 
421  // Check for bound JS functions.
422  // First part: check that the callable is a bound function whose target
423  // is {Function.prototype.call}, and which only binds a receiver.
424  if (!IsJSBoundFunction(*callable)) return kGeneric;
425  auto bound = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(callable);
426  if (bound->bound_arguments()->length() != 0) return kGeneric;
427  if (!IsJSFunction(bound->bound_target_function())) return kGeneric;
428  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi =
429  Cast<JSFunction>(bound->bound_target_function())->shared();
430  if (!sfi->HasBuiltinId()) return kGeneric;
431  if (sfi->builtin_id() != Builtin::kFunctionPrototypeCall) return kGeneric;
432  // Second part: check if the bound receiver is one of the builtins for which
433  // we have special-cased support.
434  Tagged<Object> bound_this = bound->bound_this();
435  if (!IsJSFunction(bound_this)) return kGeneric;
436  sfi = Cast<JSFunction>(bound_this)->shared();
437  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
438  int out_api_function_index = -1;
439  if (v8_flags.wasm_fast_api &&
440  IsSupportedWasmFastApiFunction(isolate, sig, sfi,
441  ReceiverKind::kFirstParamIsReceiver,
442  &out_api_function_index)) {
443  Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> func_data = sfi->api_func_data();
444  NativeModule* native_module = trusted_instance_data->native_module();
445  if (!native_module->TrySetFastApiCallTarget(
446  func_index,
447  func_data->GetCFunction(isolate, out_api_function_index))) {
448  return kGeneric;
449  }
450 #ifdef V8_USE_SIMULATOR_WITH_GENERIC_C_CALLS
451  Address c_functions[] = {func_data->GetCFunction(isolate, 0)};
452  const v8::CFunctionInfo* const c_signatures[] = {
453  func_data->GetCSignature(isolate, 0)};
454  isolate->simulator_data()->RegisterFunctionsAndSignatures(c_functions,
455  c_signatures, 1);
456 #endif // V8_USE_SIMULATOR_WITH_GENERIC_C_CALLS
457  // Store the signature of the C++ function in the native_module. We check
458  // first if the signature already exists in the native_module such that we
459  // do not create a copy of the signature unnecessarily. Since
460  // `has_fast_api_signature` and `set_fast_api_signature` don't happen
461  // atomically, it is still possible that multiple copies of the signature
462  // get created. However, the `TrySetFastApiCallTarget` above guarantees that
463  // if there are concurrent calls to `set_cast_api_signature`, then all calls
464  // would store the same signature to the native module.
465  if (!native_module->has_fast_api_signature(func_index)) {
466  // We have to use the lock of the NativeModule here because the
467  // `signature_zone` may get accessed by another module instantiation
468  // concurrently.
469  NativeModule::NativeModuleAllocationLockScope lock(native_module);
470  native_module->set_fast_api_signature(
471  func_index,
472  GetFunctionSigForFastApiImport(
473  &native_module->module()->signature_zone,
474  func_data->GetCSignature(isolate, out_api_function_index)));
475  }
476 
477  DirectHandle<HeapObject> js_signature(sfi->api_func_data()->signature(),
478  isolate);
479  DirectHandle<Object> callback_data(
480  sfi->api_func_data()->callback_data(kAcquireLoad), isolate);
481  DirectHandle<WasmFastApiCallData> fast_api_call_data =
482  isolate->factory()->NewWasmFastApiCallData(js_signature, callback_data);
483  trusted_instance_data->well_known_imports()->set(func_index,
484  *fast_api_call_data);
485  return WellKnownImport::kFastAPICall;
486  }
487  if (!sfi->HasBuiltinId()) return kGeneric;
488  switch (sfi->builtin_id()) {
489 #if V8_INTL_SUPPORT
490  case Builtin::kStringPrototypeToLocaleLowerCase:
491  if (sig->parameter_count() == 2 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
492  IsStringRef(sig->GetParam(0)) && IsStringRef(sig->GetParam(1)) &&
493  IsStringRef(sig->GetReturn(0))) {
494  DCHECK_GE(func_index, 0);
495  trusted_instance_data->well_known_imports()->set(func_index,
496  bound_this);
497  return WellKnownImport::kStringToLocaleLowerCaseStringref;
498  }
499  break;
500  case Builtin::kStringPrototypeToLowerCaseIntl:
501  if (sig->parameter_count() == 1 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
502  IsStringRef(sig->GetParam(0)) && IsStringRef(sig->GetReturn(0))) {
503  return WellKnownImport::kStringToLowerCaseStringref;
504  } else if (sig->parameter_count() == 1 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
505  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
506  sig->GetReturn(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef) {
507  return WellKnownImport::kStringToLowerCaseImported;
508  }
509  break;
510 #endif
511  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetBigInt64:
512  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI64)) {
513  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetBigInt64;
514  }
515  break;
516  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetBigUint64:
517  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI64)) {
518  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetBigUint64;
519  }
520  break;
521  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetFloat32:
522  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmF32)) {
523  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetFloat32;
524  }
525  break;
526  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetFloat64:
527  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmF64)) {
528  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetFloat64;
529  }
530  break;
531  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetInt8:
532  if (sig->parameter_count() == 2 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
533  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
534  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
535  sig->GetReturn(0) == wasm::kWasmI32) {
536  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetInt8;
537  }
538  break;
539  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetInt16:
540  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
541  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetInt16;
542  }
543  break;
544  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetInt32:
545  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
546  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetInt32;
547  }
548  break;
549  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetUint8:
550  if (sig->parameter_count() == 2 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
551  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
552  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
553  sig->GetReturn(0) == wasm::kWasmI32) {
554  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetUint8;
555  }
556  break;
557  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetUint16:
558  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
559  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetUint16;
560  }
561  break;
562  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetUint32:
563  if (IsDataViewGetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
564  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewGetUint32;
565  }
566  break;
567 
568  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetBigInt64:
569  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI64)) {
570  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetBigInt64;
571  }
572  break;
573  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetBigUint64:
574  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI64)) {
575  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetBigUint64;
576  }
577  break;
578  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetFloat32:
579  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmF32)) {
580  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetFloat32;
581  }
582  break;
583  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetFloat64:
584  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmF64)) {
585  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetFloat64;
586  }
587  break;
588  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetInt8:
589  if (sig->parameter_count() == 3 && sig->return_count() == 0 &&
590  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
591  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
592  sig->GetParam(2) == wasm::kWasmI32) {
593  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetInt8;
594  }
595  break;
596  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetInt16:
597  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
598  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetInt16;
599  }
600  break;
601  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetInt32:
602  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
603  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetInt32;
604  }
605  break;
606  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetUint8:
607  if (sig->parameter_count() == 3 && sig->return_count() == 0 &&
608  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
609  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
610  sig->GetParam(2) == wasm::kWasmI32) {
611  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetUint8;
612  }
613  break;
614  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetUint16:
615  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
616  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetUint16;
617  }
618  break;
619  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeSetUint32:
620  if (IsDataViewSetterSig(sig, wasm::kWasmI32)) {
621  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewSetUint32;
622  }
623  break;
624  case Builtin::kDataViewPrototypeGetByteLength:
625  if (sig->parameter_count() == 1 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
626  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
627  sig->GetReturn(0) == kWasmF64) {
628  return WellKnownImport::kDataViewByteLength;
629  }
630  break;
631  case Builtin::kNumberPrototypeToString:
632  if (sig->parameter_count() == 2 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
633  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
634  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
635  IsStringOrExternRef(sig->GetReturn(0))) {
636  return WellKnownImport::kIntToString;
637  }
638  if (sig->parameter_count() == 1 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
639  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmF64 &&
640  IsStringOrExternRef(sig->GetReturn(0))) {
641  return WellKnownImport::kDoubleToString;
642  }
643  break;
644  case Builtin::kStringPrototypeIndexOf:
645  // (string, string, i32) -> (i32).
646  if (sig->parameter_count() == 3 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
647  IsStringRef(sig->GetParam(0)) && IsStringRef(sig->GetParam(1)) &&
648  sig->GetParam(2) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
649  sig->GetReturn(0) == wasm::kWasmI32) {
650  return WellKnownImport::kStringIndexOf;
651  } else if (sig->parameter_count() == 3 && sig->return_count() == 1 &&
652  sig->GetParam(0) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
653  sig->GetParam(1) == wasm::kWasmExternRef &&
654  sig->GetParam(2) == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
655  sig->GetReturn(0) == wasm::kWasmI32) {
656  return WellKnownImport::kStringIndexOfImported;
657  }
658  break;
659  default:
660  break;
661  }
662  return kGeneric;
663 }
664 
665 } // namespace

683  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable) {

685  trusted_function_data_ = {};

687  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = Cast<JSFunction>(*callable_)->shared();

693 ImportCallKind ResolvedWasmImport::ComputeKind(
694  DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data, int func_index,
695  const wasm::CanonicalSig* expected_sig, CanonicalTypeIndex expected_sig_id,
696  WellKnownImport preknown_import) {
697  // If we already have a compile-time import, simply pass that through.
698  if (IsCompileTimeImport(preknown_import)) {
699  well_known_status_ = preknown_import;
700  DCHECK(IsJSFunction(*callable_));
701  DCHECK_EQ(Cast<JSFunction>(*callable_)
702  ->shared()
703  ->internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver(),
704  expected_sig->parameter_count());
705  return ImportCallKind::kJSFunction;
706  }
707  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
708  if (IsWasmSuspendingObject(*callable_)) {
709  suspend_ = kSuspend;
710  SetCallable(isolate, Cast<WasmSuspendingObject>(*callable_)->callable());
711  }
712  if (!trusted_function_data_.is_null() &&
713  IsWasmExportedFunctionData(*trusted_function_data_)) {
714  Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> data =
715  Cast<WasmExportedFunctionData>(*trusted_function_data_);
716  if (!data->MatchesSignature(expected_sig_id)) {
717  return ImportCallKind::kLinkError;
718  }
719  uint32_t function_index = static_cast<uint32_t>(data->function_index());
720  if (function_index >=
721  data->instance_data()->module()->num_imported_functions) {
722  return ImportCallKind::kWasmToWasm;
723  }
724  // Resolve the shortcut to the underlying callable and continue.
725  ImportedFunctionEntry entry(direct_handle(data->instance_data(), isolate),
726  function_index);
727  suspend_ = Cast<WasmImportData>(entry.implicit_arg())->suspend();
728  SetCallable(isolate, entry.callable());
729  }
730  if (!trusted_function_data_.is_null() &&
731  IsWasmJSFunctionData(*trusted_function_data_)) {
732  Tagged<WasmJSFunctionData> js_function_data =
733  Cast<WasmJSFunctionData>(*trusted_function_data_);
734  suspend_ = js_function_data->GetSuspend();
735  if (!js_function_data->MatchesSignature(expected_sig_id)) {
736  return ImportCallKind::kLinkError;
737  }
738  if (IsJSFunction(js_function_data->GetCallable())) {
739  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi =
740  Cast<JSFunction>(js_function_data->GetCallable())->shared();
741  if (sfi->HasWasmFunctionData(isolate)) {
742  // Special case if the underlying callable is a WasmJSFunction or
743  // WasmExportedFunction: link the outer WasmJSFunction itself and not
744  // the inner callable. Otherwise when the wrapper tiers up, we will try
745  // to link the inner WasmJSFunction/WamsExportedFunction which is
746  // incorrect.
747  return ImportCallKind::kUseCallBuiltin;
748  }
749  }
750  SetCallable(isolate, js_function_data->GetCallable());
751  }
752  if (WasmCapiFunction::IsWasmCapiFunction(*callable_)) {
753  // TODO(jkummerow): Update this to follow the style of the other kinds of
754  // functions.
755  auto capi_function = Cast<WasmCapiFunction>(callable_);
756  if (!capi_function->MatchesSignature(expected_sig_id)) {
757  return ImportCallKind::kLinkError;
758  }
759  return ImportCallKind::kWasmToCapi;
760  }
761  // Assuming we are calling to JS, check whether this would be a runtime error.
762  if (!wasm::IsJSCompatibleSignature(expected_sig)) {
763  return ImportCallKind::kRuntimeTypeError;
764  }
765  // Check if this can be a JS fast API call.
766  if (v8_flags.turbo_fast_api_calls &&
767  ResolveBoundJSFastApiFunction(expected_sig, callable_)) {
768  return ImportCallKind::kWasmToJSFastApi;
769  }
770  well_known_status_ = CheckForWellKnownImport(
771  trusted_instance_data, func_index, callable_, expected_sig);
772  if (well_known_status_ == WellKnownImport::kLinkError) {
773  return ImportCallKind::kLinkError;
774  }
775  // TODO(jkummerow): It would be nice to return {kJSFunction} here
776  // whenever {well_known_status_ != kGeneric}, so that the generic wrapper
777  // can be used instead of a compiled wrapper; but that requires adding
778  // support for calling bound functions to the generic wrapper first.
779 
780  // For JavaScript calls, determine whether the target has an arity match.
781  if (IsJSFunction(*callable_)) {
782  auto function = Cast<JSFunction>(callable_);
783  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(), isolate);
784 
785  if (IsClassConstructor(shared->kind())) {
786  // Class constructor will throw anyway.
787  return ImportCallKind::kUseCallBuiltin;
788  }
789 
790  return ImportCallKind::kJSFunction;
791  }
792  // Unknown case. Use the call builtin.
793  return ImportCallKind::kUseCallBuiltin;
794 }

821  void MaterializeDescriptorOptions(MaybeDirectHandle<JSReceiver> ffi) {
822  if (!v8_flags.wasm_explicit_prototypes) return;
823  if (!it_.ok()) return;
824  MaterializeDescriptorOptionsImpl(ffi);
825  if (!it_.ok()) thrower_->CompileFailed(it_.error());
826  }

828  // For the "modular" variant of the proposal.
829  // Specified to run right after the "start" function, before instantiation
830  // completes.
831  void ConfigurePrototypes_Modular() {
832  if (!it_.ok()) return;
833  ConfigurePrototypes_Modular_Impl();
834  if (!it_.ok()) thrower_->CompileFailed(it_.error());
835  }
836 
837  // For the "direct" variant of the proposal.
838  // Specified to run unobservably (possibly lazily); this initial
839  // implementation runs it eagerly before the "start" function (which is the
840  // earliest point that might observe that it happened).
841  // Note: if we want to run it later, we'll have to split out validation.
842  void ConfigurePrototypes_Direct() {
843  if (!v8_flags.wasm_implicit_prototypes) return;
844  if (!it_.ok()) return;
845  ConfigurePrototypes_Direct_Impl();
846  if (!it_.ok()) thrower_->CompileFailed(it_.error());
847  }

849  private:
850  using ImportEntry = DescriptorsSectionIterator::ImportEntry;
851  using DeclEntry = DescriptorsSectionIterator::DeclEntry;
852  using GlobalEntry = DescriptorsSectionIterator::GlobalEntry;
853  using ProtoConfig = DescriptorsSectionIterator::ProtoConfig;
854  using Method = DescriptorsSectionIterator::Method;

856  ///////////////// Implementation of the public interface. ////////////////////
857 
858  void MaterializeDescriptorOptionsImpl(MaybeDirectHandle<JSReceiver> ffi) {
859  WireBytesRef module_name_ref = it_.module_name();
860  DirectHandle<String> module_name = GetString(module_name_ref);
861  size_t num_entries = it_.NumImportAndDeclEntries();
862  uint32_t current_entry_index = 0;
863  DirectHandleVector<JSPrototype> entries(isolate_, num_entries);
864 
865  // Import entries subsection.
866  if (it_.has_import_entry()) {
867  // Prepare the "module" sub-object of the imports object.
868  if (ffi.is_null()) {
869  thrower_->TypeError(
870  "Imports argument must be present and must be an object");
871  return;
872  }
873  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> module;
874  if (!GetImportedObject(ffi.ToHandleChecked(), module_name, "module",
875  &module)) {
876  return;
877  }
878 
879  do {
880  ImportEntry import_entry = it_.NextImportEntry();
881  WireBytesRef name = import_entry.name();
882  if (!import_entry.ok()) return;
883  DirectHandle<String> import_name = GetString(name);
884  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> prototype;
885  if (!GetImportedObject(module, import_name, "import", &prototype)) {
886  return;
887  }
888  DirectHandle<WasmDescriptorOptions> descriptor_options =
889  WasmDescriptorOptions::New(isolate_, prototype);
890  entries[current_entry_index++] = prototype;
891  while (import_entry.has_export()) {
892  uint32_t export_index = import_entry.NextExport(max_import_index_);
893  if (!import_entry.ok()) return;
894  sanitized_imports_[export_index] = descriptor_options;
895  }
896  } while (it_.ok() && it_.has_import_entry());
897  }
898 
899  // Decl entries subsection.
900  while (it_.ok() && it_.has_decl_entry()) {
901  DeclEntry decl_entry = it_.NextDeclEntry();
902  if (!it_.ok()) return;
903  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> parent = isolate_->initial_object_prototype();
904  if (decl_entry.has_parent()) {
905  uint32_t parent_index = decl_entry.Parent(current_entry_index);
906  if (!it_.ok()) return;
907  parent = entries[parent_index];
908  }
909  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype =
910  WasmStruct::AllocatePrototype(isolate_, parent);
911  DirectHandle<WasmDescriptorOptions> descriptor_options =
912  WasmDescriptorOptions::New(isolate_, prototype);
913  entries[current_entry_index++] = descriptor_options;
914  while (decl_entry.has_export()) {
915  uint32_t export_index = decl_entry.NextExport(max_import_index_);
916  if (!decl_entry.ok()) return;
917  sanitized_imports_[export_index] = descriptor_options;
918  }
919  }
920  }
921 
922  void ConfigurePrototypes_Modular_Impl() {
923  DCHECK(!trusted_instance_data_.is_null());
924  if (!v8_flags.wasm_implicit_prototypes) it_.SkipToProtoConfigs();
925  while (it_.has_proto_config()) {
926  ProtoConfig proto_config = it_.NextProtoConfig(max_import_index_);
927  if (!it_.ok()) return;
928  uint32_t import_index = proto_config.import_index();
929  if (!IsWasmDescriptorOptions(*sanitized_imports_[import_index])) {
930  thrower_->LinkError("import %u must be a descriptor", import_index);
931  return;
932  }
933  DirectHandle<WasmDescriptorOptions> desc =
934  Cast<WasmDescriptorOptions>(sanitized_imports_[import_index]);
935  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> prototype(Cast<JSReceiver>(desc->prototype()),
936  isolate_);
937 
938  if (proto_config.has_method()) {
939  ToDictionaryMode(prototype, proto_config.estimated_number_of_methods());
940  }
941 
942  while (proto_config.has_method()) {
943  Method method = proto_config.NextMethod(max_export_index_);
944  if (!it_.ok()) return;
945  if (!InstallMethodByExportIndex(prototype, method)) return;
946  }
947 
948  // Constructor function, if any.
949  if (!proto_config.has_constructor()) continue;
950  auto [constructor_name_ref, constructor_index] =
951  proto_config.Constructor(max_export_index_);
952  if (!it_.ok()) return;
953  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function;
954  if (!GetExportedFunction(constructor_index).ToHandle(&function)) return;
955  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor =
956  MakeConstructor(constructor_name_ref, function, prototype);
957 
958  // Static methods/accessors on the constructor, if any.
959  if (!proto_config.has_static()) continue;
960  int num_methods = proto_config.estimated_number_of_statics();
961  JSObject::NormalizeProperties(isolate_, constructor,
962  KEEP_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES, num_methods,
963  "Wasm constructor setup");
964  do {
965  Method staticmethod = proto_config.NextStatic(max_export_index_);
966  if (!it_.ok()) return;
967  if (!InstallMethodByExportIndex(constructor, staticmethod)) return;
968  } while (proto_config.has_static());
969  }
970  }
971 
972  void ConfigurePrototypes_Direct_Impl() {
973  DCHECK(!trusted_instance_data_.is_null());
974  if (!v8_flags.wasm_explicit_prototypes) it_.SkipToGlobalEntries();
975  uint32_t max_global_index = static_cast<uint32_t>(module_->globals.size());
976  uint32_t max_function_index =
977  static_cast<uint32_t>(module_->functions.size());
978  while (it_.has_global_entry()) {
979  // Fetch the descriptor from the global and extract its RTT.
980  GlobalEntry global_entry = it_.NextGlobalEntry(max_global_index);
981  if (!it_.ok()) return;
982  Tagged<Map> rtt =
983  GetRttInGlobal(global_entry.global_index(), "installing a prototype");
984  if (rtt.is_null()) return;
985  DirectHandle<Map> described_rtt(rtt, isolate_);
986  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> parent = isolate_->initial_object_prototype();
987  if (global_entry.has_parent()) {
988  uint32_t parent_index = global_entry.Parent();
989  if (!it_.ok()) return;
990  Tagged<Map> parent_rtt =
991  GetRttInGlobal(parent_index, "being a prototype parent");
992  if (parent_rtt.is_null()) return;
993  parent = direct_handle(parent_rtt->prototype(), isolate_);
994  }
995 
996  // Allocate, install, and populate the prototype as requested.
997  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype =
998  WasmStruct::AllocatePrototype(isolate_, parent);
999  Map::SetPrototype(isolate_, described_rtt, prototype);
1000 
1001  if (global_entry.has_method()) {
1002  ToDictionaryMode(prototype, global_entry.estimated_number_of_methods());
1003  }
1004  while (global_entry.has_method()) {
1005  Method method = global_entry.NextMethod(max_function_index);
1006  if (!it_.ok()) return;
1007  if (!InstallMethodByFunctionIndex(prototype, method)) return;
1008  }
1009 
1010  // Constructor function, if any.
1011  if (!global_entry.has_constructor()) continue;
1012  auto [constructor_name_ref, constructor_index] =
1013  global_entry.Constructor(max_function_index);
1014  if (!it_.ok()) return;
1015  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = GetFunction(constructor_index);
1016  DCHECK_EQ(function->length(),
1017  module_->functions[constructor_index].sig->parameter_count());
1018  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor =
1019  MakeConstructor(constructor_name_ref, function, prototype);
1020 
1021  // Static methods/accessors on the constructor, if any.
1022  if (!global_entry.has_static()) continue;
1023  ToDictionaryMode(constructor, global_entry.estimated_number_of_statics());
1024  do {
1025  Method staticmethod = global_entry.NextStatic(max_function_index);
1026  if (!it_.ok()) return;
1027  if (!InstallMethodByFunctionIndex(constructor, staticmethod)) return;
1028  } while (global_entry.has_static());
1029  }
1030  }

1039  bool GetImportedObject(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> holder,
1040  DirectHandle<String> name,
1041  const char* description_for_error,
1042  DirectHandle<JSReceiver>* out) {
1043  DirectHandle<Object> value;
1044  if (!Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate_, holder, name)
1045  .ToHandle(&value) ||
1046  !TryCast<JSReceiver>(value, out)) {
1047  thrower_->LinkError("%s: %s not found or not an object",
1048  name->ToCString().get(), description_for_error);
1049  return false;
1050  }
1051  return true;
1052  }

1054  // Note: this is only safe to call after {ProcessExports} has run!
1055  MaybeDirectHandle<WasmExportedFunction> GetExportedFunction(
1056  uint32_t export_index) {
1057  const WasmExport& exp = module_->export_table[export_index];
1058  if (exp.kind != kExternalFunction) {
1059  thrower_->LinkError("export %u must be a function", export_index);
1060  return {};
1061  }
1062  bool shared = module_->function_is_shared(exp.index);
1063  Tagged<Object> funcref =
1064  (shared ? shared_instance_data_ : trusted_instance_data_)
1065  ->func_refs()
1066  ->get(exp.index);
1067  DCHECK(IsWasmFuncRef(funcref));
1068  Tagged<WasmInternalFunction> internal_func =
1069  Cast<WasmFuncRef>(funcref)->internal(isolate_);
1070  return direct_handle(Cast<WasmExportedFunction>(internal_func->external()),
1071  isolate_);
1072  }
1073 
1074  DirectHandle<WasmExportedFunction> GetFunction(uint32_t index) {
1075  bool shared = module_->function_is_shared(index);
1076  DirectHandle<WasmFuncRef> funcref =
1077  WasmTrustedInstanceData::GetOrCreateFuncRef(
1078  isolate_, shared ? shared_instance_data_ : trusted_instance_data_,
1079  index);
1080  DirectHandle<WasmInternalFunction> internal_function(
1081  funcref->internal(isolate_), isolate_);
1082  return Cast<WasmExportedFunction>(
1083  WasmInternalFunction::GetOrCreateExternal(internal_function));
1084  }

1086  Tagged<Map> GetRttInGlobal(uint32_t global_index,
1087  const char* description_for_error) {
1088  const WasmGlobal& global = module_->globals[global_index];
1089  if (!IsDescriptorGlobal(global)) {
1090  thrower_->CompileError("global %u has unsuitable type for %s",
1091  global_index, description_for_error);
1092  return {};
1093  }
1094  auto data = global.shared ? shared_instance_data_ : trusted_instance_data_;
1095  Tagged<Object> value = data->tagged_globals_buffer()->get(global.offset);
1096  return Cast<WasmStruct>(value)->described_rtt();
1097  }
1098 
1099  bool IsDescriptorGlobal(const WasmGlobal& global) {
1100  return !global.mutability && global.initializer_ends_with_struct_new &&
1101  global.type.ref_type_kind() == RefTypeKind::kStruct &&
1102  global.type.has_index() &&
1103  module_->type(global.type.ref_index()).is_descriptor();
1104  }
1105 
1106  DirectHandle<JSFunction> MakeConstructor(
1107  WireBytesRef name_ref, DirectHandle<JSFunction> wasm_function,
1108  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> prototype) {
1109  DirectHandle<String> name = GetString(name_ref);
1110  DirectHandle<Context> context = isolate_->factory()->NewBuiltinContext(
1111  isolate_->native_context(), kConstructorFunctionContextLength);
1112  context->SetNoCell(kConstructorFunctionContextSlot, *wasm_function);
1113  Builtin code = Builtin::kWasmConstructorWrapper;
1114  int length = wasm_function->length();
1115  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi =
1116  isolate_->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(name, code, length,
1117  kDontAdapt);
1118  sfi->set_native(true);
1119  sfi->set_language_mode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
1120  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor =
1121  Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate_, sfi, context}
1122  .set_map(isolate_->strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map())
1123  .Build();
1124  constructor->set_prototype_or_initial_map(*prototype, kReleaseStore);
1125  prototype->map()->SetConstructor(*constructor);
1126  InstallExport(name, constructor);
1127  return constructor;
1128  }

1146  bool InstallMethodByFunctionIndex(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1147  const Method& method) {

1149  return InstallMethodImpl(object, method, function);

1151  bool InstallMethodImpl(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, const Method& method,
1152  DirectHandle<WasmExportedFunction> function) {
1153  DirectHandle<String> method_name = GetString(method.name);
1154  if (!method.is_static) {
1155  WasmExportedFunction::MarkAsReceiverIsFirstParam(isolate_, function);
1156  }
1157  PropertyDescriptor prop;
1158  prop.set_enumerable(false);
1159  prop.set_configurable(true);
1160  if (method.kind == Method::kMethod) {
1161  prop.set_writable(true);
1162  prop.set_value(function);
1163  } else if (method.kind == Method::kGetter) {
1164  prop.set_get(function);
1165  } else if (method.kind == Method::kSetter) {
1166  prop.set_set(function);
1167  } else {
1168  UNREACHABLE(); // Ruled out by validation.
1169  }
1170  if (!JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(isolate_, object, method_name, &prop,
1171  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
1172  .FromMaybe(false)) {
1173  DCHECK(isolate_->has_exception());
1174  return false;
1175  }
1176  return true;
1177  }

1180  PropertyDetails details(

1183  PropertyConstness::kMutable);

1186  JSObject::AddDataElement(isolate_, exports_object_, array_index, value,
1187  details.attributes());
1188  } else {
1189  JSObject::SetNormalizedProperty(exports_object_, name, value, details);
1190  }
1191  }

1298  // Creation of a Wasm instance with {Build()} is split into several phases:
1299  //
1300  // First phase: initializes (trusted) objects, so if it fails halfway
1301  // through (when validation errors are encountered), it must not leave
1302  // pointers to half-initialized objects elsewhere in memory (e.g. it
1303  // must not register the instance in "uses" lists, nor write active
1304  // element segments into imported tables).
1305  Maybe<bool> Build_Phase1(const DisallowJavascriptExecution& no_js);
1306  // The last part of the first phase finalizes initialization of trusted
1307  // objects and creates pointers from elsewhere to them. This sub-phase
1308  // can never fail, but should still happen under the lifetime of the
1309  // TrustedPointerPublishingScope.
1310  // When reaching the end of this phase, all created objects (for the
1311  // instance, tables, globals, etc) must be in fully initialized and
1312  // self-consistent state, ready to execute user code (such as the "start"
1313  // function, or fallible user-provided initializers).
1314  void Build_Phase1_Infallible();
1315  // Second phase: runs module-provided initializers and as such can fail,
1316  // but may assume that just-created objects have been initialized to a
1317  // consistent state, and *must* assume that these objects are already
1318  // reachable from elsewhere (so must no longer be made inaccessible on
1319  // failure).
1320  Maybe<bool> Build_Phase2();

1403 MaybeDirectHandle<WasmInstanceObject> InstantiateToInstanceObject(
1404  Isolate* isolate, ErrorThrower* thrower,
1405  DirectHandle<WasmModuleObject> module_object,
1406  MaybeDirectHandle<JSReceiver> imports,
1407  MaybeDirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> memory_buffer) {
1408  v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId context_id =
1409  isolate->GetOrRegisterRecorderContextId(isolate->native_context());
1410  InstanceBuilder builder(isolate, context_id, thrower, module_object, imports,
1411  memory_buffer);
1412  MaybeDirectHandle<WasmInstanceObject> instance_object = builder.Build();
1413  if (!instance_object.is_null()) {
1414  const std::shared_ptr<NativeModule>& native_module =
1415  module_object->shared_native_module();
1416  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_pgo_to_file &&
1417  native_module->ShouldPgoDataBeWritten() &&
1418  native_module->module()->num_declared_functions > 0) {

1422  builder.ConfigurePrototypes_Modular()) {
1423  builder.FinalizeExportsObject(instance_object);

1425  }
1426  }
1427  DCHECK(isolate->has_exception() || thrower->error());
1428  return {};

1452 // Build an instance, in all of its glory.
1453 MaybeDirectHandle<WasmInstanceObject> InstanceBuilder::Build() {
1454  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.wasm.detailed"),
1455  "wasm.InstanceBuilder.Build");
1456  // Will check whether {ffi_} is available.
1457  SanitizeImports();
1458  if (thrower_->error()) return {};
1459 
1460  // From here on, we expect the build pipeline to run without exiting to JS.
1461  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate_);
1462  // Start a timer for instantiation time, if we have a high resolution timer.
1463  base::ElapsedTimer timer;
1464  if (base::TimeTicks::IsHighResolution()) {
1465  timer.Start();
1466  }
1467  v8::metrics::WasmModuleInstantiated wasm_module_instantiated;
1468 
1469  // Phase 1: uses a {TrustedPointerPublishingScope} to make the new,
1470  // partially-initialized instance inaccessible in case of failure.
1471  if (Build_Phase1(no_js).IsNothing()) return {};
1472  // Phase 2: assumes that the new instance is already sufficiently
1473  // consistently initialized to be exposed to user code.
1474  if (Build_Phase2().IsNothing()) return {};
1475 
1476  wasm_module_instantiated.success = true;
1477  wasm_module_instantiated.imported_function_count =
1478  module_->num_imported_functions;
1479  if (timer.IsStarted()) {
1480  base::TimeDelta instantiation_time = timer.Elapsed();
1481  wasm_module_instantiated.wall_clock_duration_in_us =
1482  instantiation_time.InMicroseconds();
1483  SELECT_WASM_COUNTER(isolate_->counters(), module_->origin, wasm_instantiate,
1484  module_time)
1485  ->AddTimedSample(instantiation_time);
1486  isolate_->metrics_recorder()->DelayMainThreadEvent(wasm_module_instantiated,
1487  context_id_);
1488  }
1489 
1490  return direct_handle(trusted_data_->instance_object(), isolate_);
1491 }
1492 
1493 Maybe<bool> InstanceBuilder::Build_Phase1(
1494  const DisallowJavascriptExecution& no_js) {
1495  // Any trusted pointers created here will be zapped unless instantiation
1496  // successfully runs to completion, to prevent trusted objects that violate
1497  // their own internal invariants because they're only partially-initialized
1498  // from becoming accessible to untrusted code.
1499  // We assume failure for now, and will update to success later.
1500  TrustedPointerPublishingScope publish_trusted_objects(isolate_, no_js);
1501  publish_trusted_objects.MarkFailure();
1502  NativeModule* native_module = module_object_->native_module();
1503 
1504  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1505  // Create the WebAssembly.Instance object.
1506  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1507  TRACE("New module instantiation for %p\n", native_module);
1508  trusted_data_ = WasmTrustedInstanceData::New(isolate_, module_object_, false);
1509  bool shared = module_object_->module()->has_shared_part;
1510  if (shared) {
1511  // For now, allocate the shared part in non-shared space. We do not need it
1512  // in shared space yet since no shared objects point to it.
1513  // TODO(42204563): This will change once we introduce shared globals,
1514  // tables, or functions.
1515  shared_trusted_data_ =
1516  WasmTrustedInstanceData::New(isolate_, module_object_, false);
1517  trusted_data_->set_shared_part(*shared_trusted_data_);
1518  }
1519 
1520  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1521  // Set up the memory buffers and memory objects and attach them to the
1522  // instance.
1523  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1524  if (is_asmjs_module(module_)) {
1525  CHECK_EQ(1, module_->memories.size());
1526  DirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> buffer;
1527  if (!asmjs_memory_buffer_.ToHandle(&buffer)) {
1528  // Use an empty JSArrayBuffer for degenerate asm.js modules.
1529  MaybeDirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> new_buffer =
1530  isolate_->factory()->NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
1531  0, InitializedFlag::kUninitialized);
1532  if (!new_buffer.ToHandle(&buffer)) {
1533  thrower_->RangeError("Out of memory: asm.js memory");
1534  return {};
1535  }
1536  buffer->set_is_detachable(false);
1537  }
1538  // asm.js instantiation should have changed the state of the buffer (or we
1539  // set it above).
1540  CHECK(!buffer->is_detachable());
1541 
1542  // The maximum number of pages isn't strictly necessary for memory
1543  // objects used for asm.js, as they are never visible, but we might
1544  // as well make it accurate.
1545  auto maximum_pages =
1546  static_cast<int>(RoundUp(buffer->byte_length(), wasm::kWasmPageSize) /
1547  wasm::kWasmPageSize);
1548  DirectHandle<WasmMemoryObject> memory_object = WasmMemoryObject::New(
1549  isolate_, buffer, maximum_pages, AddressType::kI32);
1550  constexpr int kMemoryIndexZero = 0;
1551  trusted_data_->memory_objects()->set(kMemoryIndexZero, *memory_object);
1552  } else {
1553  CHECK(asmjs_memory_buffer_.is_null());
1554  DirectHandle<FixedArray> memory_objects{trusted_data_->memory_objects(),
1555  isolate_};
1556  // First process all imported memories, then allocate non-imported ones.
1557  if (!ProcessImportedMemories(memory_objects)) {
1558  return {};
1559  }
1560  // Actual Wasm modules can have multiple memories.
1561  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmMemories <= kMaxUInt32);
1562  uint32_t num_memories = static_cast<uint32_t>(module_->memories.size());
1563  for (uint32_t memory_index = 0; memory_index < num_memories;
1564  ++memory_index) {
1565  if (!IsUndefined(memory_objects->get(memory_index))) continue;
1566  DirectHandle<WasmMemoryObject> memory_object;
1567  if (AllocateMemory(memory_index).ToHandle(&memory_object)) {
1568  memory_objects->set(memory_index, *memory_object);
1569  } else {
1570  DCHECK(isolate_->has_exception() || thrower_->error());
1571  return {};
1572  }
1573  }
1574  }
1575 
1576  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1577  // Set up the globals for the new instance.
1578  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1579  uint32_t untagged_globals_buffer_size = module_->untagged_globals_buffer_size;
1580  if (untagged_globals_buffer_size > 0) {
1581  MaybeDirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> result =
1582  isolate_->factory()->NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
1583  untagged_globals_buffer_size, InitializedFlag::kZeroInitialized,
1584  AllocationType::kOld);
1585 
1586  if (!result.ToHandle(&untagged_globals_)) {
1587  thrower_->RangeError("Out of memory: wasm globals");
1588  return {};
1589  }
1590 
1591  trusted_data_->set_untagged_globals_buffer(*untagged_globals_);
1592  trusted_data_->set_globals_start(
1593  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(untagged_globals_->backing_store()));
1594 
1595  // TODO(42204563): Do this only if we have a shared untagged global.
1596  // TODO(42204563): Reinstate once we support shared globals.
1597  /* if (shared) {
1598  MaybeDirectHandle<JSArrayBuffer> shared_result =
1599  isolate_->factory()->NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
1600  untagged_globals_buffer_size, InitializedFlag::kZeroInitialized,
1601  AllocationType::kSharedOld);
1602 
1603  if (!shared_result.ToHandle(&shared_untagged_globals_)) {
1604  thrower_->RangeError("Out of memory: wasm globals");
1605  return {};
1606  }
1607 
1608  shared_trusted_data->set_untagged_globals_buffer(
1609  *shared_untagged_globals_);
1610  shared_trusted_data->set_globals_start(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(
1611  shared_untagged_globals_->backing_store()));
1612  }*/
1613  }
1614 
1615  uint32_t tagged_globals_buffer_size = module_->tagged_globals_buffer_size;
1616  if (tagged_globals_buffer_size > 0) {
1617  tagged_globals_ = isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1618  static_cast<int>(tagged_globals_buffer_size));
1619  trusted_data_->set_tagged_globals_buffer(*tagged_globals_);
1620  if (shared) {
1621  shared_tagged_globals_ = isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1622  static_cast<int>(tagged_globals_buffer_size),
1623  AllocationType::kSharedOld);
1624  shared_trusted_data_->set_tagged_globals_buffer(*shared_tagged_globals_);
1625  }
1626  }
1627 
1628  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1629  // Set up the array of references to imported globals' array buffers.
1630  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1631  if (module_->num_imported_mutable_globals > 0) {
1632  // TODO(binji): This allocates one slot for each mutable global, which is
1633  // more than required if multiple globals are imported from the same
1634  // module.
1635  DirectHandle<FixedArray> buffers_array = isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1636  module_->num_imported_mutable_globals, AllocationType::kOld);
1637  trusted_data_->set_imported_mutable_globals_buffers(*buffers_array);
1638  if (shared) {
1639  DirectHandle<FixedArray> shared_buffers_array =
1640  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1641  module_->num_imported_mutable_globals,
1642  AllocationType::kSharedOld);
1643  shared_trusted_data_->set_imported_mutable_globals_buffers(
1644  *shared_buffers_array);
1645  }
1646  }
1647 
1648  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1649  // Set up the tag table used for exception tag checks.
1650  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1651  int tags_count = static_cast<int>(module_->tags.size());
1652  if (tags_count > 0) {
1653  DirectHandle<FixedArray> tag_table =
1654  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(tags_count, AllocationType::kOld);
1655  trusted_data_->set_tags_table(*tag_table);
1656  tags_wrappers_.resize(tags_count);
1657  if (shared) {
1658  DirectHandle<FixedArray> shared_tag_table =
1659  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(tags_count,
1660  AllocationType::kSharedOld);
1661  shared_trusted_data_->set_tags_table(*shared_tag_table);
1662  shared_tags_wrappers_.resize(tags_count);
1663  }
1664  }
1665 
1666  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1667  // Set up table storage space, and initialize it for non-imported tables.
1668  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1669  int table_count = static_cast<int>(module_->tables.size());
1670  if (table_count == 0) {
1671  trusted_data_->set_tables(*isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1672  if (shared) {
1673  shared_trusted_data_->set_tables(
1674  *isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1675  }
1676  } else {
1677  DirectHandle<FixedArray> tables =
1678  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(table_count);
1679  DirectHandle<ProtectedFixedArray> dispatch_tables =
1680  isolate_->factory()->NewProtectedFixedArray(table_count);
1681  trusted_data_->set_tables(*tables);
1682  trusted_data_->set_dispatch_tables(*dispatch_tables);
1683  DirectHandle<FixedArray> shared_tables;
1684  DirectHandle<ProtectedFixedArray> shared_dispatch_tables;
1685  if (shared) {
1686  shared_tables = isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1687  table_count, AllocationType::kSharedOld);
1688  shared_dispatch_tables =
1689  isolate_->factory()->NewProtectedFixedArray(table_count);
1690  shared_trusted_data_->set_tables(*shared_tables);
1691  shared_trusted_data_->set_dispatch_tables(*shared_dispatch_tables);
1692  }
1693  for (int i = module_->num_imported_tables; i < table_count; i++) {
1694  const WasmTable& table = module_->tables[i];
1695  CanonicalValueType canonical_type = module_->canonical_type(table.type);
1696  // Initialize tables with null for now. We will initialize non-defaultable
1697  // tables later, in {SetTableInitialValues}.
1698  DirectHandle<WasmDispatchTable> dispatch_table;
1699  DirectHandle<WasmTableObject> table_obj = WasmTableObject::New(
1700  isolate_, trusted_data(table.shared), table.type, canonical_type,
1701  table.initial_size, table.has_maximum_size, table.maximum_size,
1702  table.type.use_wasm_null()
1703  ? DirectHandle<HeapObject>{isolate_->factory()->wasm_null()}
1704  : DirectHandle<HeapObject>{isolate_->factory()->null_value()},
1705  table.address_type, &dispatch_table);
1706  (table.shared ? shared_tables : tables)->set(i, *table_obj);
1707  if (!dispatch_table.is_null()) {
1708  (table.shared ? shared_dispatch_tables : dispatch_tables)
1709  ->set(i, *dispatch_table);
1710  if (i == 0) {
1711  trusted_data(table.shared)->set_dispatch_table0(*dispatch_table);
1712  }
1713  }
1714  }
1715  }
1716 
1717  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1718  // Process the imports for the module.
1719  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1720  if (!module_->import_table.empty()) {
1721  int num_imported_functions = ProcessImports();
1722  if (num_imported_functions < 0) return {};
1723  }
1724 
1725  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1726  // Create maps for managed objects (GC proposal).
1727  // Must happen before {InitGlobals} because globals can refer to these maps.
1728  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1729  if (!module_->isorecursive_canonical_type_ids.empty()) {
1730  // Make sure all canonical indices have been set.
1731  DCHECK(module_->MaxCanonicalTypeIndex().valid());
1732  TypeCanonicalizer::PrepareForCanonicalTypeId(
1733  isolate_, module_->MaxCanonicalTypeIndex());
1734  }
1735  DirectHandle<FixedArray> non_shared_maps = isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1736  static_cast<int>(module_->types.size()));
1737  DirectHandle<FixedArray> shared_maps =
1738  shared ? isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1739  static_cast<int>(module_->types.size()),
1740  AllocationType::kSharedOld)
1741  : DirectHandle<FixedArray>();
1742  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < module_->types.size(); index++) {
1743  bool map_is_shared = module_->types[index].is_shared;
1744  CreateMapForType(isolate_, module_, ModuleTypeIndex{index},
1745  map_is_shared ? shared_maps : non_shared_maps);
1746  }
1747  trusted_data_->set_managed_object_maps(*non_shared_maps);
1748  if (shared) shared_trusted_data_->set_managed_object_maps(*shared_maps);
1749 #if DEBUG
1750  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < module_->types.size(); i++) {
1751  DirectHandle<FixedArray> maps =
1752  module_->types[i].is_shared ? shared_maps : non_shared_maps;
1753  Tagged<Object> o = maps->get(i);
1754  DCHECK(IsMap(o));
1755  Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(o);
1756  ModuleTypeIndex index{i};
1757  if (module_->has_signature(index)) {
1758  DCHECK_EQ(map->instance_type(), WASM_FUNC_REF_TYPE);
1759  } else if (module_->has_array(index)) {
1760  DCHECK_EQ(map->instance_type(), WASM_ARRAY_TYPE);
1761  } else if (module_->has_struct(index)) {
1762  DCHECK_EQ(map->instance_type(), WASM_STRUCT_TYPE);
1763  }
1764  }
1765 #endif
1766 
1767  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1768  // Allocate the array that will hold type feedback vectors.
1769  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1770  if (v8_flags.wasm_inlining) {
1771  int num_functions = static_cast<int>(module_->num_declared_functions);
1772  // Zero-fill the array so we can do a quick Smi-check to test if a given
1773  // slot was initialized.
1774  DirectHandle<FixedArray> vectors =
1775  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArrayWithZeroes(num_functions,
1776  AllocationType::kOld);
1777  trusted_data_->set_feedback_vectors(*vectors);
1778  if (shared) {
1779  DirectHandle<FixedArray> shared_vectors =
1780  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArrayWithZeroes(
1781  num_functions, AllocationType::kSharedOld);
1782  shared_trusted_data_->set_feedback_vectors(*shared_vectors);
1783  }
1784  }
1785 
1786  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1787  // Process the initialization for the module's globals.
1788  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1789  InitGlobals();
1790 
1791  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1792  // Initialize non-defaultable tables.
1793  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1794  SetTableInitialValues();
1795 
1796  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1797  // Initialize the tags table.
1798  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1799  if (tags_count > 0) {
1800  InitializeTags();
1801  }
1802 
1803  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1804  // Set up the exports object for the new instance.
1805  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1806  ProcessExports();
1807  if (thrower_->error()) return {};
1808 
1809  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1810  // Set up uninitialized element segments.
1811  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1812  if (!module_->elem_segments.empty()) {
1813  DirectHandle<FixedArray> elements = isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1814  static_cast<int>(module_->elem_segments.size()));
1815  DirectHandle<FixedArray> shared_elements =
1816  shared ? isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1817  static_cast<int>(module_->elem_segments.size()),
1818  AllocationType::kSharedOld)
1819  : DirectHandle<FixedArray>();
1820  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < module_->elem_segments.size(); i++) {
1821  // Initialize declarative segments as empty. The rest remain
1822  // uninitialized.
1823  bool is_declarative = module_->elem_segments[i].status ==
1824  WasmElemSegment::kStatusDeclarative;
1825  (module_->elem_segments[i].shared ? shared_elements : elements)
1826  ->set(i, is_declarative
1827  ? Cast<Object>(*isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array())
1828  : *isolate_->factory()->undefined_value());
1829  }
1830  trusted_data_->set_element_segments(*elements);
1831  if (shared) shared_trusted_data_->set_element_segments(*shared_elements);
1832  }
1833 
1834  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1835  // Create a wrapper for the start function.
1836  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1837  if (module_->start_function_index >= 0) {
1838  int start_index = module_->start_function_index;
1839  auto& function = module_->functions[start_index];
1840 
1841  DCHECK(start_function_.is_null());
1842  if (function.imported) {
1843  ImportedFunctionEntry entry(trusted_data_, module_->start_function_index);
1844  Tagged<Object> callable = entry.maybe_callable();
1845  if (IsJSFunction(callable)) {
1846  // If the start function was imported and calls into Blink, we have
1847  // to pretend that the V8 API was used to enter its correct context.
1848  // In order to simplify entering the context in {ExecuteStartFunction}
1849  // below, we just record the callable as the start function.
1850  start_function_ = direct_handle(Cast<JSFunction>(callable), isolate_);
1851  }
1852  }
1853  if (start_function_.is_null()) {
1854  // TODO(clemensb): Don't generate an exported function for the start
1855  // function. Use CWasmEntry instead.
1856  bool function_is_shared = module_->type(function.sig_index).is_shared;
1857  DirectHandle<WasmFuncRef> func_ref =
1858  WasmTrustedInstanceData::GetOrCreateFuncRef(
1859  isolate_, trusted_data(function_is_shared), start_index);
1860  DirectHandle<WasmInternalFunction> internal{func_ref->internal(isolate_),
1861  isolate_};
1862  start_function_ = WasmInternalFunction::GetOrCreateExternal(internal);
1863  }
1864  }
1865 
1866  DCHECK(!isolate_->has_exception());
1867  TRACE("Successfully built instance for module %p\n",
1868  module_object_->native_module());
1869 
1870 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1871  // Skip this event because not (yet) supported by Chromium.
1872 
1873  // v8::metrics::WasmInterpreterJitStatus jit_status;
1874  // jit_status.jitless = v8_flags.wasm_jitless;
1875  // isolate_->metrics_recorder()->DelayMainThreadEvent(jit_status,
1876  // context_id_);
1877 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1878 
1879  publish_trusted_objects.MarkSuccess();
1880  Build_Phase1_Infallible();
1881  return Just(true);
1882 }

1884 void InstanceBuilder::Build_Phase1_Infallible() {
1885  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1886  // Register with memories.
1887  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1888  size_t num_memories = module_->memories.size();
1889  DirectHandle<FixedArray> memory_objects{trusted_data_->memory_objects(),
1890  isolate_};
1891  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < num_memories; i++) {
1892  DirectHandle<WasmMemoryObject> memory{
1893  Cast<WasmMemoryObject>(memory_objects->get(i)), isolate_};
1894  WasmMemoryObject::UseInInstance(isolate_, memory, trusted_data_,
1895  shared_trusted_data_, i);
1896  }
1897 
1898  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1899  // Register with tables.
1900  //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1901  size_t num_tables = module_->tables.size();
1902  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < num_tables; i++) {
1903  const WasmTable& table = module_->tables[i];
1904  DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> data_part =
1905  trusted_data(table.shared);
1906  Tagged<Object> maybe_dispatch_table = data_part->dispatch_tables()->get(i);
1907  if (maybe_dispatch_table == Smi::zero()) continue; // Not a function table.
1908  DirectHandle<WasmDispatchTable> dispatch_table{
1909  Cast<WasmDispatchTable>(maybe_dispatch_table), isolate_};
1910  WasmDispatchTable::AddUse(isolate_, dispatch_table, data_part, i);
1911  }
1912 }

1942 bool InstanceBuilder::ExecuteStartFunction() {
1943  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.wasm.detailed"),
1944  "wasm.ExecuteStartFunction");
1945  if (start_function_.is_null()) return true; // No start function.
1946 
1947  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
1948  // In case the start function calls out to Blink, we have to make sure that
1949  // the correct "entered context" is available. This is the equivalent of
1950  // v8::Context::Enter() and must happen in addition to the function call
1951  // sequence doing the compiled version of "isolate->set_context(...)".
1952  HandleScopeImplementer* hsi = isolate_->handle_scope_implementer();
1953  hsi->EnterContext(start_function_->native_context());
1954 
1955  // Call the JS function.
1956  DirectHandle<Object> undefined = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
1957  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> retval =
1958  Execution::Call(isolate_, start_function_, undefined, {});
1959  hsi->LeaveContext();
1960  // {start_function_} has to be called only once.
1961  start_function_ = {};
1962 
1963  if (retval.is_null()) {
1964  DCHECK(isolate_->has_exception());
1965  return false;
1966  }
1967  return true;
1968 }

1970 // Look up an import value in the {ffi_} object.
1971 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> InstanceBuilder::LookupImport(
1972  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<String> module_name,
1973  DirectHandle<String> import_name) {
1974  // The caller checked that the ffi object is present; and we checked in
1975  // the JS-API layer that the ffi object, if present, is a JSObject.
1976  DCHECK(!ffi_.is_null());
1977  // Look up the module first.
1978  DirectHandle<Object> module;
1979  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> module_recv;
1980  if (!Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate_, ffi_.ToHandleChecked(),
1981  module_name)
1982  .ToHandle(&module) ||
1983  !TryCast<JSReceiver>(module, &module_recv)) {
1984  const char* error = module.is_null()
1985  ? "module not found"
1986  : "module is not an object or function";
1987  thrower_->TypeError("%s: %s", ImportName(index, module_name).c_str(),
1988  error);
1989  return {};
1990  }
1991 
1992  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> value =
1993  Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate_, module_recv, import_name);
1994  if (value.is_null()) {
1995  thrower_->LinkError("%s: import not found", ImportName(index).c_str());
1996  return {};
1997  }
1998 
1999  return value;
2000 }

2002 namespace {
2003 bool HasDefaultToNumberBehaviour(Isolate* isolate,
2004  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
2005  // Disallow providing a [Symbol.toPrimitive] member.
2006  LookupIterator to_primitive_it{isolate, function,
2007  isolate->factory()->to_primitive_symbol()};
2008  if (to_primitive_it.state() != LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND) return false;
2009 
2010  // The {valueOf} member must be the default "ObjectPrototypeValueOf".
2011  LookupIterator value_of_it{isolate, function,
2012  isolate->factory()->valueOf_string()};
2013  if (value_of_it.state() != LookupIterator::DATA) return false;
2014  DirectHandle<Object> value_of = value_of_it.GetDataValue();
2015  if (!IsJSFunction(*value_of)) return false;
2016  Builtin value_of_builtin_id =
2017  Cast<JSFunction>(value_of)->code(isolate)->builtin_id();
2018  if (value_of_builtin_id != Builtin::kObjectPrototypeValueOf) return false;
2019 
2020  // The {toString} member must be the default "FunctionPrototypeToString".
2021  LookupIterator to_string_it{isolate, function,
2022  isolate->factory()->toString_string()};
2023  if (to_string_it.state() != LookupIterator::DATA) return false;
2024  DirectHandle<Object> to_string = to_string_it.GetDataValue();
2025  if (!IsJSFunction(*to_string)) return false;
2026  Builtin to_string_builtin_id =
2027  Cast<JSFunction>(to_string)->code(isolate)->builtin_id();
2028  if (to_string_builtin_id != Builtin::kFunctionPrototypeToString) return false;
2029 
2030  // Just a default function, which will convert to "Nan". Accept this.
2031  return true;
2032 }

2035  if (is_error(value)) {
2036  thrower->RuntimeError("%s",
2037  MessageFormatter::TemplateString(to_error(value)));
2038  return true;

2044 // Look up an import value in the {ffi_} object specifically for linking an
2045 // asm.js module. This only performs non-observable lookups, which allows
2046 // falling back to JavaScript proper (and hence re-executing all lookups) if
2047 // module instantiation fails.
2048 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> InstanceBuilder::LookupImportAsm(
2049  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<String> import_name) {
2050  // The caller checked that the ffi object is present.
2051  DCHECK(!ffi_.is_null());
2052 
2053  // Perform lookup of the given {import_name} without causing any observable
2054  // side-effect. We only accept accesses that resolve to data properties,
2055  // which is indicated by the asm.js spec in section 7 ("Linking") as well.
2056  PropertyKey key(isolate_, Cast<Name>(import_name));
2057  LookupIterator it(isolate_, ffi_.ToHandleChecked(), key);
2058  switch (it.state()) {
2059  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
2060  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
2061  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
2062  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
2063  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
2064  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
2065  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
2066  thrower_->LinkError("%s: not a data property",
2067  ImportName(index, import_name).c_str());
2068  return {};
2069  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
2070  // Accepting missing properties as undefined does not cause any
2071  // observable difference from JavaScript semantics, we are lenient.
2072  return isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
2073  case LookupIterator::DATA: {
2074  DirectHandle<Object> value = it.GetDataValue();
2075  // For legacy reasons, we accept functions for imported globals (see
2076  // {ProcessImportedGlobal}), but only if we can easily determine that
2077  // their Number-conversion is side effect free and returns NaN (which is
2078  // the case as long as "valueOf" (or others) are not overwritten).
2079  if (IsJSFunction(*value) &&
2080  module_->import_table[index].kind == kExternalGlobal &&
2081  !HasDefaultToNumberBehaviour(isolate_, Cast<JSFunction>(value))) {
2082  thrower_->LinkError("%s: function has special ToNumber behaviour",
2083  ImportName(index, import_name).c_str());
2084  return {};
2085  }
2086  return value;
2087  }
2088  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
2089  UNREACHABLE();
2090  }
2091 }

2093 // Load data segments into the memory.
2094 // TODO(14616): Consider what to do with shared memories.
2095 void InstanceBuilder::LoadDataSegments() {
2096  base::Vector<const uint8_t> wire_bytes =
2097  module_object_->native_module()->wire_bytes();
2098  for (const WasmDataSegment& segment : module_->data_segments) {
2099  uint32_t size = segment.source.length();
2100 
2101  // Passive segments are not copied during instantiation.
2102  if (!segment.active) continue;
2103 
2104  const WasmMemory& dst_memory = module_->memories[segment.memory_index];
2105  size_t dest_offset;
2106  ValueOrError result = EvaluateConstantExpression(
2107  &init_expr_zone_, segment.dest_addr,
2108  dst_memory.is_memory64() ? kWasmI64 : kWasmI32, module_, isolate_,
2109  trusted_data_, shared_trusted_data_);
2110  if (MaybeMarkError(result, thrower_)) return;
2111  if (dst_memory.is_memory64()) {
2112  uint64_t dest_offset_64 = to_value(result).to_u64();
2113 
2114  // Clamp to {std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max()}, which is always an
2115  // invalid offset, so we always fail the bounds check below.
2116  DCHECK_GT(std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max(), dst_memory.max_memory_size);
2117  dest_offset = static_cast<size_t>(std::min(
2118  dest_offset_64, uint64_t{std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max()}));
2119  } else {
2120  dest_offset = to_value(result).to_u32();
2121  }
2122 
2123  size_t memory_size = trusted_data_->memory_size(segment.memory_index);
2124  if (!base::IsInBounds<size_t>(dest_offset, size, memory_size)) {
2125  size_t segment_index = &segment - module_->data_segments.data();
2126  thrower_->RuntimeError(
2127  "data segment %zu is out of bounds (offset %zu, "
2128  "length %u, memory size %zu)",
2129  segment_index, dest_offset, size, memory_size);
2130  return;
2131  }
2132 
2133  uint8_t* memory_base = trusted_data_->memory_base(segment.memory_index);
2134  std::memcpy(memory_base + dest_offset,
2135  wire_bytes.begin() + segment.source.offset(), size);
2136  }
2137 }

2141  TRACE("init [globals_start=%p + %u] = %s, type = %s\n",
2142  global.type.is_reference()

2144  : raw_buffer_ptr(untagged_globals_, 0),

2146  DCHECK(global.mutability

2156 // Returns the name, Builtin ID, and "length" (in the JSFunction sense, i.e.
2157 // number of parameters) for the function representing the given import.
2158 std::tuple<const char*, Builtin, int> NameBuiltinLength(WellKnownImport wki) {
2159 #define CASE(CamelName, name, length) \
2160  case WellKnownImport::kString##CamelName: \
2161  return std::make_tuple(name, Builtin::kWebAssemblyString##CamelName, length)
2162  switch (wki) {
2163  CASE(Cast, "cast", 1);
2164  CASE(CharCodeAt, "charCodeAt", 2);
2165  CASE(CodePointAt, "codePointAt", 2);
2166  CASE(Compare, "compare", 2);
2167  CASE(Concat, "concat", 2);
2168  CASE(Equals, "equals", 2);
2169  CASE(FromCharCode, "fromCharCode", 1);
2170  CASE(FromCodePoint, "fromCodePoint", 1);
2171  CASE(FromUtf8Array, "decodeStringFromUTF8Array", 3);
2172  CASE(FromWtf16Array, "fromCharCodeArray", 3);
2173  CASE(IntoUtf8Array, "encodeStringIntoUTF8Array", 3);
2174  CASE(Length, "length", 1);
2175  CASE(MeasureUtf8, "measureStringAsUTF8", 1);
2176  CASE(Substring, "substring", 3);
2177  CASE(Test, "test", 1);
2178  CASE(ToUtf8Array, "encodeStringToUTF8Array", 1);
2179  CASE(ToWtf16Array, "intoCharCodeArray", 3);
2180  default:
2181  UNREACHABLE(); // Only call this for compile-time imports.
2182  }
2183 #undef CASE
2184 }

2186 DirectHandle<JSFunction> CreateFunctionForCompileTimeImport(
2187  Isolate* isolate, WellKnownImport wki) {
2188  auto [name, builtin, length] = NameBuiltinLength(wki);
2189  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
2190  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context(isolate->native_context());
2191  DirectHandle<Map> map = isolate->strict_function_without_prototype_map();
2192  DirectHandle<String> name_str = factory->InternalizeUtf8String(name);
2193  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
2194  factory->NewSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(name_str, builtin, length,
2195  kAdapt);
2196  info->set_native(true);
2197  info->set_language_mode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
2198  DirectHandle<JSFunction> fun =
2199  Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, context}.set_map(map).Build();
2200  return fun;
2201 }
